ple, we find that\nthese are likely due to selection biases and are consistent with no intrinsic\ncorrelations within the sample. This protocluster sample supports the strong\nevolutionary trend observed in the Ly$\\alpha$ escape fraction and suggest that\nlower redshift LAEs can be on average significantly more dusty that their\ncounterparts at higher redshift.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Mar 2021 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 12 Aug 2021 10:02:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-17"}
