 low star-formation rates in this\ngalaxy. Previous authors have already noted that the X-ray halo of J2345-0449\nimplies a baryon fraction near the cosmic average, which is very high for a\ngalaxy. We contrast this finding with other, equally massive baryon-rich spiral\ngalaxies without prominent radio sources. Most of the baryons in these galaxies\nare in stars, not in the halos. We also discuss the implications of our results\nfor our general understanding of AGN feedback in massive galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Mar 2021 20:02:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-04"}
